$ Shell command: adduser
@ adduser

code {
sudo addgroup someGroup
sudu adduser --ingroup someGroup someUser
code }

{ TODO

  On an Oracle Linux 8.10 system, I found `adduser` to be a symlink to `→ Linux/shell/commands/useradd`:
code {
$ → Linux/shell/commands/ls/l $(→ Linux/shell/commands/which adduser useradd)
lrwxrwxrwx 1 root root      7 Apr  9  2024 /usr/sbin/adduser -> useradd
-rwxr-xr-x 1 root root 151720 Apr  9  2024 /usr/sbin/useradd
code }

}

